legal_basis: Sections 20(1)(c) and 20(1)(d) of the Access to Information Act
evidence_assessment: insufficient evidence of probable harm beyond speculation
decision_reasoning: lack of tangible evidence showing reasonable expectation of harm
application_details: applicant argued that disclosing the agreement would harm its competitive position and interfere with negotiations
result_of_case: court dismissed the application, ordering costs against the applicant
procedure_followed: Applicant filed for judicial review after receiving notice of disclosure intent. Federal Court evaluated evidence of probable harm
